mac Finnerty]]|IRL|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|14:08.88\n|align=\"center\"|13:54.01\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|&mdash;\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Khmees Abdalla Seif Eldin]]|SUD|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|DNQ\n|align=\"center\"|14:15.21 \n|-\n|align=\"center\"|&mdash;\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Jos\u00e9 Ramos (athlete)|Jos\u00e9 Ramos]]|POR|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|14:24.81 \n|align=\"center\"|14:17.26\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|&mdash;\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Shadrack Hoff]]|RSA|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|14:16.14 \n|align=\"center\"|14:05.97\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|&mdash;\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Jim Spivey]]|USA|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|14:27.72 \n|align=\"center\"|13:53.16\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|&mdash;\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Julian Paynter]]|AUS|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|14:23.60 \n|align=\"center\"|14:00.25\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|&mdash;\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Adalberto Garc\u00eda]]|BRA|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|DNQ\n|align=\"center\"|14:28.64 \n|-\n|align=\"center\"|&mdash;\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Manuel Pancorbo]]|ESP|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|14:39.64 \n|align=\"center\"|13:57.42\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|&mdash;\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Sid'Ahmed Ould Mohamedou]]|MTN|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|DNQ\n|align=\"center\"|15:29.16 \n|-\n|align=\"center\"|&mdash;\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Henry Moyo (athlete)|Henry Moyo]]|MAW|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|DNQ\n|align=\"center\"|14:30.53 \n|-\n|align=\"center\"|&mdash;\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Matt Giusto]]|USA|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|DNQ\n|align=\"center\"|14:30.76 \n|-\n|align=\"center\"|&mdash;\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[William Rold\u00e1n]]|COL|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|DNQ\n|align=\"center\"|14:39.50 \n|-\n|align=\"center\"|&mdash;\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Aboukar Hassan Adani]]|SOM|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|DNQ\n|align=\"center\"|15:19.80 \n|-\n|align=\"center\"|&mdash;\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Haile Gebrselassie]]|ETH|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|-\n|align=\"center\"|DNS\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|&mdash;\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Armando Quintanilla]]|MEX|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|-\n|align=\"center\"|DNS\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|&mdash;\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Luis Jesus]]|POR|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|-\n|align=\"center\"|DNS\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|&mdash;\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Aloys Nizigama]]|BDI|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|-\n|align=\"center\"|DNS\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|&mdash;\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Alyan al-Qahtani]]|KSA|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|-\n|align=\"center\"|DNS\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[1994 European Championships in Athletics \u2013 Men's 5000 metres|1994 Men's European Championships 5.000 metres (Helsinki)]]\n*[[1995 World Championships in Athletics \u2013 Men's 5000 metres|1995 Men's World Championships 5.000 metres (Gothenburg)]]\n*[[1997 World Championships in Athletics \u2013 Men's 5000 metres|1997 Men's World Championships 5.000 metres (Athens)]]\n*[[1998 European Championships in Athletics \u2013 Men's 5000 metres|1998 Men's European Championships 5.000 metres (Budapest)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070503054122/http://www.olympic-museum.de/o-reports/report1996.htm Official Report]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070928000052/http://todor66.com/olim/1996/Athletics/Men_5000m.html Results]\n\n{{Olympics5000metres}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Athletics At The 1996 Summer Olympics - Men's 5000 Metres}}\n[[Category:Athletics at the 1996 Summer Olympics|5]]\n[[Category:5000 metres at the Olympics]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Olympic event\n|event = Men's 5000 metres\n|games = 1996 Summer\n|image =\n|caption =\n|venue = [[Centennial Olympic Stadium]]\n|date = {{Date|1996-7-31}} (heats)<br />{{Date|1996-8-1}} (semi-finals)<br />{{Date|1996-8-3}} (final)\n|competitors = 37\n|nations = 23\n|win_value = 13:07.96\n|longnames = yes\n|gold = [[Venuste Niyongabo]]\n|goldNOC = BDI\n|silver = [[Paul Bitok]]\n|silverNOC = KEN\n|bronze = [[Khalid Boulami]]\n|bronzeNOC = MAR\n|prev = [[Athletics at the 1992 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 5000 metres|1992]]\n|next = [[Athletics at the 2000 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 5000 metres|2000]]\n}}\n{{AthleticsAt1996SummerOlympics}}\n\nThese are the official results of the '''[[Athletics at the 1996 Summer Olympics|men's 5000 metres]]''' at the '''[[1996 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Atlanta, Georgia]]. The event took place between 31 July and 3 August.<ref name=\"SR\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/1996/ATH/mens-5000-metres.html |title=Athletics at the 1996 Atlanta Games: Men's 5000 metres |accessdate=11 November 2017 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref>\n\n==Medalists==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:110%;\" width=\"35%\"\n|-\n|{{OlympicGoldMedalist|[[Venuste Niyongabo]]|BDI|1996 Summer}}\n|-\n|{{OlympicSilverMedalist|[[Paul Bitok]]|KEN|1996 Summer}}\n|-\n|{{OlympicBronzeMedalist|[[Khalid Boulami]]|MAR|1996 Summer}}\n|}\n\n==Summary==\n\nAfter a diverse semi-final round where one heat ran a modes 14 minute strategic race and the other ran over thirty seconds faster, some athletes had an easier time of qualifying for the final.\n\nAt the gun, the entire Moroccan team went to the front, but then controlled the pace.  After a lap at the back of the pack, Kenyan [[Tom Nyariki]] ran around the field to take the lead.  German [[Dieter Baumann]] hung on his shoulder as it looked like an early attempt to steal the race with a quick breakaway.  Several others in the field scrambled forward while Nyariki, shadowed by his teammate [[Shem Kororia]] pushed the pace, exchanging the lead position and stringing out the field into single file.  Home team American [[Bob Kennedy (runner)|Bob Kennedy]] marked this action hovering around second place to the thrill of the crowd.  With four laps to go, after an exchange of Kenyan leaders, Burundi's [[V\u00e9nuste Niyongabo]] moved into second place, squeezing back Kennedy into third.  Over the next lap, Nyariki and Moroccan [[Brahim Lahlafi]] got past Kennedy.  Just before two laps to go, Kennedy ran around the group and into the lead.  Kennedy led for the first 300 metres of the penultimate lap before Niyongabo passed him coming off the turn, followed by the designated kickers who had protected their interests at the back of the pack;  [[Paul Bitok]] (Kenya), [[Khalid Boulami]] (Morocco) and Baumann.  But as one of the fastest 1500 meter runners in the world at the time, Niyongabo had the position and more speed, opening up a 5 metre gap on Boulami.  At the beginning of the final turn, Bitok got around Boulami and everybody sprinted for home.  Nobody was able to make any progress except that Niyongabo slowed on the final straight to celebrate Burundi's first gold medal.\n\n==Records==\nThese were the standing world and Olympic records (in minutes) prior to the 1996 Summer Olympics.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|- \n! World Record\n| 12:44.39\n| {{flagicon|ETH|1991}} [[Haile Gebrselassie]]\n| [[Z\u00fcrich]] ([[Switzerland|SUI]])\n| August 16, 1995\n|-\n! Olympic Record\n| 13:05.59\n| {{flagicon|MAR}} [[Sa\u00efd Aouita]]\n| [[Los Angeles, California|Los Angeles]] ([[United States|USA]])\n| August 11, 1984\n|}\n\n==Final classification==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|-\n!RANK !!align=\"left\" style=\"width: 20em\"|NAME ATHLETE!!FINAL!!SEMI!!HEAT\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|[[Image:Med 1.png]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Venuste Niyongabo]]|BDI|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|'''13:07.96'''\n|align=\"center\"|14:03.48\n|align=\"center\"|13:54.53\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|[[Image:Med 2.png]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Paul Bitok]]|KEN|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|'''13:08.16'''\n|align=\"center\"|13:27.61\n|align=\"center\"|13:54.45\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|[[Image:Med 3.png]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Khalid Boulami]]|MAR|1996 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|'''13:08.37'''\n|align=\"center\"|13:29.72\n|align=\"center\"|13:54.72\n|-\n|align=\"cent