r\"|DNS\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[1994 European Championships in Athletics \u2013 Men's 5000 metres|1994 Men's European Championships 5.000 metres (Helsinki)]]\n*[[1995 World Championships in Athletics \u2013 Men's 5000 metres|1995 Men's World Championships 5.000 metres (Gothenburg)]]\n*[[1997 World Championships in Athletics \u2013 Men's 5000 metres|1997 Men's World Championships 5.000 metres (Athens)]]\n*[[1998 European Championships in Athletics \u2013 Men's 5000 metres|1998 Men's European Championships 5.000 metres (Budapest)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070503054122/http://www.olympic-museum.de/o-reports/report1996.htm Official Report]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070928000052/http://todor66.com/olim/1996/Athletics/Men_5000m.html Results]\n\n{{Olympics5000metres}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Athletics At The 1996 Summer Olympics - Men's 5000 Metres}}\n[[Category:Athletics at the 1996 Summer Olympics|5]]\n[[Category:5000 metres at the Olympics]]\n", "name_user": "Faceloffs", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Athletics_at_the_1996_Summer_Olympics_%E2%80%93_Men%27s_5000_metres"}
{"title_page": "National Youth Icon Award", "text_new": "{{short description|Award is given to individuals who contribute towards social welfare}}\n{{Infobox award\n| name           = National Youth Icon Award\n| current_awards =\n| image          = \n| alt            =\n| caption        = National Youth Icon Award 2019\n| description    = \n| presenter      = World Youth Summit\n| host           =\n| date           = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| location       =\n| country        = [[India]]\n| year           = 2019\n| website      = {{URL|http://www.saarcyouth.org/}}\n}}\n\nThe '''National Youth Icon Award''' is awarded annually by the International Youth Committee (IYC), a [[United Nations]] accredited organization, at the World Youth Summit. The award is given for the young people globally in recognition of their development work and their contribution towards developing a peaceful, fairer, prosperous and sustainable future that meets the [[Sustainable Development Goals]] (SDGs) of [[United Nations]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://epaper.dailymirror.lk/epaper/viewer.aspx|title=Vithoshan receives 2019 National Youth Icon Award |newspaper=[[The Daily Mirror (Sri Lanka)]]|date=22 Oct 2019 |accessdate=22 Oct 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://starofmysore.com/national-youth-icon-awardee/|title=National Youth Icon Awardee|newspaper=[[Star of Mysore]]|date=27 October  2019|accessdate=27 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://ahduni.edu.in/chm/heritage-management-alumnus-received-national-youth-icon-award/|title=Heritage Management alumnus Received National Youth Icon Award|newspaper=[[Ahmedabad University]]|date=27 October  2019|accessdate=27 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://ahduni.edu.in/chm/heritage-management-alumnus-received-national-youth-icon-award/|title=Heritage Management alumnus Received National Youth Icon Award|newspaper=[[Ahmedabad University]]|date=27 October  2019|accessdate=27 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nLaunched in the year 2016, the World Youth Summit honors young people who have made significant contributions in professional or voluntary capacity covering areas such as [[poverty reduction]], [[democracy]], conflict resolution and prevention, [[environmental preservation]], [[community service]] and [[social development]]. The National Youth Icon Award consists of a Gold Pin Medal, a citation and a scroll.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://thenortheasttoday.com/tag/national-youth-icon-award/|title=Manipur\u2019s Monika Ingudam among 79 to receive National youth icon award 2019|newspaper=[[The Northeast Today]]|date= 29 Sep 2019|accessdate=29 Sep 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.dailyexcelsior.com/poonch-social-worker-receives-national-youth-icon-award/page12-894/|title=Muzaffar Ahmed of Poonch being conferred National Youth Icon Award-2019 at New Delhi.|newspaper=[[Daily Excelsior]]|date= 29 Sep 2019|accessdate=29 Sep 2019}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\nThe National Youth Icon award was first introduced in 2016 by the International Youth Committee (IYC), which is an organization accredited by the [[United Nations]]. The award is conferred to 70 young individuals globally, setting high standards for their inspiring work and services contributed towards achieving the (SDGs) of the [[United Nations]].The award gives an international recognition to these individuals who dedicated their lives to communities, nations and the world. Powerful, outstanding & influential youth role models in the fields of [[social work]], [[education]], [[human rights]], [[peace]], [[philanthropy]], [[business]], sports, [[health]], [[entertainment]], [[youth empowerment]], and popular arts and [[culture]] are honored with the National Youth Icon Award. In 2017 the International Youth Committee (IYC) also introduced the [[Asia Inspiration Award]] for recognizing the inspirational achievements of young individuals in Asia.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thedailystar.net/city/news/sri-lanka-host-2nd-south-asian-youth-summit-1637302|title= 2nd South Asian Youth Summit in Sri Lanka|newspaper=[[The Daily Star (Bangladesh)]] |date=23 September 2018 |accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.colombopage.com/archive_18B/Sep23_1537674160CH.php|title= Sri Lanka to host South Asian Youth Summit 2018 |newspaper=Colombopage|date=23 September 2018 |accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailynews.lk/2018/09/18/local/162912/south-asian-youth-summit-be-held-colombo |title=South Asian Youth Summit to be held in Colombo|newspaper=[[Daily News (Sri Lanka)|Daily News]] |date=18 September 2018 |accessdate=18 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.colombopage.com/archive_18B/Sep23_1537674160CH.php|title= Sri Lanka to host South Asian Youth Summit 2018 |newspaper=Colombopage|date=23 September 2018 |accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.island.lk/index.php?page_cat=article-details&page=article-details&code_title=191694|title=Lanka hosts South Asian Youth Summit|newspaper=[[The Island (Sri Lanka)|The Island]] |date=18 September 2018 |accessdate=18 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2018/12/09/news/michelle-dilhara-wins-asia-inspiration-award-2018|title=Michelle Dilhara wins Asia Inspiration Award 2018|newspaper=[[Sunday Observer (Sri Lanka)|Sunday Observer]] |date=9 December 2018 |accessdate=9 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://sundayobserver.lk/2018/12/16/youth-observer/mesmerising-michelle|title=Mesmerising Michelle|publisher=[[Sunday Observer (Sri Lanka)|Sunday Observer]]|date=16 December 2018|accessdate=16 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navhindtimes.in/author-priya-dalvi-gets-asia-inspiration-award-2018-at-sri-lanka/|title=Author Priya Dalvi gets \u2018Asia Inspiration Award 2018\u2019 at Sri Lanka|publisher=[[The Navhind Times]]|date=2 January 2019|accessdate=2 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailynews.lk/2019/01/10/tc/173752/inspiring-act |title=An inspiring 'act'!|newspaper=[[Daily News (Sri Lanka)|Daily News]] |date=10 January 2019 |accessdate=10 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://thenortheasttoday.com/assam-entrepreneur-makes-nation-proud-selected-for-asia-inspiration-award/|title=Assam entrepreneur makes nation proud, selected for Asia Inspiration Award|newspaper=[[The Northeast Today]] |date=20 July 2018 |accessdate=20 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n== National Youth Icon Award 2019 ==\n\nThe World Youth Summit 2019 was held on September 27, 2019, at the Constitution Club of India, [[New Delhi]], under the theme of \"Achieving SDGs by 2030: Moving from Policy to Action.\" 81 young individuals who were performed to be the next leaders  across the world conferred with the National Youth Icon Award 2019 by International Youth Committee (IYC). Dignitaries such as [[Gaur Gopal Das]] (International life coach), Ms. [[Nusrat Jahan]], Actor & Honorable MP of Republic of India, Breshna Musazai from [[Afghanistan]] and [[Dinesh Subasinghe]] joined the World Youth Summit 2019.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thebetterindia.com/163312/anil-pradhan-education-innovation-odisha/anil-pradhan-national-youth-icon/|title=Muzaffar Ahmed of Poonch being conferred National Youth Icon Award-2019 at New Delhi.|newspaper=[[The Better India]]|date= 29 Sep 2019|accessdate=29 Sep 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://gossip.hirufm.lk/37916/2019/10/michelle-dilhara.html|title=Popular actress Michelle Dilhara receives an International Award again|publisher=[[Hiru TV]] |date=2 October 2019 |accessdate=2 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.deshaya.lk/article/52/%E0%B7%84%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%BB/13968/%E0%B6%86%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%9C%E0%B7%9A-%E0%B6%A2%E0%B7%93%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%BA-%E0%B6%85%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%8A%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%9A-%E0%B6%B8%E0%B6%B8%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%8A--%E0%B6%89%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%8F---|title=My life is also like Arthur Fleck's in Joker Film|newspaper=Deshaya|date=8 May 2019  |accessdate=8 Dec 2019}}</ref><ref name=Alternative123>{{cite web|url=http://www.ft.lk/lifestyle/The-Theory-of-Alternative-Social-Cogwheel-by-Michelle-Dilhara/8-696198|title=The Theory of Alternative Social Cogwheel by Michelle Dilhara|date=24 February 2020|publisher=[[Daily FT]]|accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"ceylontoday11\">{{cite news|url=https://ceylontoday.lk/features-more/4150|title=Through the Eyes of a Humanitarian|newspaper=[[Ceylon Today]]|date=11 November 2019|first=Priyangwada|last=Perera|accessdate=11 November 2019}}</ref> \n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n*{{Official website|http://iyc-hq.org/national-youth-icon-award/}}\n* [https://iyc.org.in/ IYC Official website]\n\n\n[[Category:2018 conferences]]\n[[Category:2018 in international relations]]\n[[Category:Award ceremonies]]\n[[Category:Indian awards]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Award is given to individuals who contribute towards social welfare}}\n{{Infobox award\n| name           = National Youth Icon Award\n| current_awards =\n| image          = \n| alt            =\n| caption        = National Youth Icon Award 2019\n| description    = \n| presenter      = World Youth Summit\n| host           =\n| date           = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| location       =\n| country        = [[India]]\n| year           = 2019\n| website      = {{URL|http://www.saarcyouth.org/}}\n}}\n\nThe '''National Youth Icon Award''' is awarded annually by the International Youth Committee (IYC), a [[United Nations]] accredited organization, at the World Youth Summit. The award is given for the young people globally in recognition of their development work and their contribution towards developing a peaceful, fairer, prosperous and sustainable future that meets the [[Sustainable Development Goals]] (SDGs) of [[United Nations]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://epaper.dailymirror.lk/epaper/viewer.aspx|title=Vithoshan receives 2019 National Youth Icon Award |newspaper=[[The Daily Mirror (Sri Lanka)]]|date=22 Oct 2019 |accessdate=22 Oct 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://starofmysore.com/national-youth-icon-awardee/|title=National Youth Icon Awardee|newspaper=[[Star of Mysore]]|date=27 October  2019|accessdate=27 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://ahduni.edu.in/chm/heritage-management-alumnus-received-national-youth-icon-award/|title=Heritage Management alumnus Received National Youth Icon Award|newspaper=[[Ahmedabad University]]|date=27 October  2019|accessdate=27 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://ahduni.edu.in/chm/heritage-management-alumnus-received-national-youth-icon-award/|title=Heritage Management alumnus Received National Youth Icon Award|newspaper=[[Ahmedabad University]]|date=27 October  2019|accessdate=27 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nLaunched in the year 2016, the World Youth Summit honors young people who have made significant contributions in professional or voluntary capacity covering areas such as [[poverty reduction]], [[democracy]], conflict resolution and prevention, [[environmental preservation]], [[community service]] and [[social development]]. The National Youth Icon Award consists of a Gold Pin Medal, a citation and a scroll.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://thenortheasttoday.com/tag/national-youth-icon-award/|title=Manipur\u2019s Monika Ingudam among 79 to receive National youth icon award 2019|newspaper=[[The Northeast Today]]|date= 29 Sep 2019|accessdate=29 Sep 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.dailyexcelsior.com/poonch-social-worker-receives-national-youth-icon-award/page12-894/|title=Muzaffar Ahmed of Poonch being conferred National Youth Icon Award-2019 at New Delhi.|newspaper=[[Daily Excelsior]]|date= 29 Sep 2019|accessdate=29 Sep 2019}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\nThe National Youth Icon award was first introduced in 2016 by the International Youth Committee (IYC), which is an organization accredited by the [[United Nations]]. The award is conferred to 70 young individuals globally, setting high standards for their inspiring work and services contributed towards achieving the (SDGs) of the [[United Nations]].The award gives an international recognition to these individuals who dedicated their lives to communities, nations and the world. Powerful, outstanding & influential youth role models in the fields of [[social work]], [[education]], [[human rights]], [[peace]], [[philanthropy]], [[business]], sports, [[health]], [[entertainment]], [[youth empowerment]], and popular arts and [[culture]] are honored with the National Youth Icon Award. In 2017 the International Youth Committee (IYC) also introduced the [[Asia Inspiration Award]] for recognizing the inspirational achievements of young individuals in Asia.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thedailystar.net/city/news/sri-lanka-host-2nd-south-asian-youth-summit-1637302|title= 2nd South Asian Youth Summit in Sri Lanka|newspaper=[[The Daily Star (Bangladesh)]] |date=23 September 2018 |accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.colombopage.com/archive_18B/Sep23_1537674160CH.php|title= Sri Lanka to host South Asian Youth Summit 2018 |newspaper=Colombopage|date=23 September 2018 |accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailynews.lk/2018/09/18/local/162912/south-asian-youth-summit-be-held-colombo |title=South Asian Youth Summit to be held in Colombo|newspaper=[[Daily News (Sri Lanka)|Daily News]] |date=18 September 2018 |accessdate=18 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.colombopage.com/archive_18B/Sep23_1537674160CH.php|title= Sri Lanka to host South Asian Youth Summit 2018 |newspaper=Colombopage|date=23 September 2018 |accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.island.lk/index.php?page_cat=article-details&page=article-details&code_title=191694|title=Lanka hosts South Asian Youth Summit|newspaper=[[The Island (Sri Lanka)|The Island]] |date=18 September 2018 |accessdate=18 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2018/12/09/news/michelle-dilhara-wins-asia-inspiration-award-2018|title=Michelle Dilhara wins Asia Inspiration Award 2018|newspaper=[[Sunday Observer (Sri Lanka)|Sunday Observer]] |date=9 December 2018 |accessdate=9 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://sundayobserver.lk/2018/12/16/youth-observer/mesmerising-michelle|title=Mesmerising Michelle|publisher=[[Sunday Observer (Sri Lanka)|Sunday Observer]]|date=16 December 2018|accessdate=16 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navhindtimes.in/author-priya-dalvi-gets-asia-inspiration-award-2018-at-sri-lanka/|title=Author Priya Dalvi gets \u2018Asia Inspiration Award 2018\u2019 at Sri Lanka|publisher=[[The Navhind Times]]|date=2 January 2019|accessdate=2 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailynews.lk/2019/01/10/tc/173752/inspiring-act |title=An inspiring 'act'!|newspaper=[[Daily News (Sri Lanka)|Daily News]] |date=10 January 2019 |accessdate=10 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://thenortheasttoday.com/assam-entrepreneur-makes-nation-proud-selected-for-asia-inspiration-award/|title=Assam entrepreneur makes nation proud, selected for Asia Inspiration Award|newspaper=[[The Northeast Today]] |date=20 July 2018 |accessdate=20 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n== National Youth Icon Award 2019 ==\n\nThe World Youth Summit 2019 was held on September 27, 2019, at the Constitution Club of India, [[New Delhi]], under the theme of \"Achieving SDGs by 2030: Moving from Policy to Action.\" 81 young individuals who were performed to be the next leaders  across the world conferred with the National Youth Icon Award 2019 by International Youth Committee (IYC). Dignitaries such as [[Gaur Gopal Das]] (International life coach), Ms. [[Nusrat Jahan]], Actor & Honorable MP of Republic of India , Breshna Musazai from [[Afghanistan]] and [[Dinesh Subasinghe]] joined the World Youth Summit 2019.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thebetterindia.com/163312/anil-pradhan-education-innovation-odisha/anil-pradhan-national-youth-icon/|title=Muzaffar Ahmed of Poonch being conferred National Youth Icon Award-2019 at New Delhi.|newspaper=[[The Better India]]|date= 29 Sep 2019|accessdate=29 Sep 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://gossip.hirufm.lk/37916/2019/10/michelle-dilhara.html|title=Popular actress Michelle Dilhara receives an International Award again|publisher=[[Hiru TV]] |date=2 October 2019 |accessdate=2 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.deshaya.lk/article/52/%E0%B7%84%E0%B6%AF%E0%B7%83%E0%B6%BB/13968/%E0%B6%86%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%BB%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%9C%E0%B7%9A-%E0%B6%A2%E0%B7%93%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%92%E0%B6%AD%E0%B6%BA-%E0%B6%85%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%8A%E0%B7%83%E0%B7%9A-%E0%B6%B8%E0%B6%B8%E0%B6%AD%E0%B7%8A--%E0%B6%89%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%8A%E0%B6%B1%E0%B7%80%E0%B7%8F---|title=My life is also like Arthur Fleck's in Joker Film|newspaper=Deshaya|date=8 May 2019  |accessdate=8 Dec 2019}}</ref><ref name=Alternative123>{{cite web|url=http://www.ft.lk/lifestyle/The-Theory-of-Alternative-Social-Cogwheel-by-Michelle-Dilhara/8-696198|title=The Theory of Alternative Social Cogwheel by Michelle Dilhara|date=24 February 2020|publisher=[[Daily FT]]|accessdate=24 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"ceylontoday11\">{{cite news|url=https://ceylontoday.lk/features-more/4150|title=Through the Eyes of a Humanitarian|newspaper=[[Ceylon Today]]|date=11 November 2019|first=Priyangwada|last=Perera|accessdate=11 November 2019}}</ref> \n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n*{{Official website|http://iyc-hq.org/national-youth-icon-award/}}\n* [https://iyc.org.in/ IYC Official website]\n\n\n[[Category:2018 conferences]]\n[[Category:2018 in international relations]]\n[[Category:Award ceremonies]]\n[[Category:Indian awards]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eNational Youth Icon Award 2019:Cleanu